Introduction

10X10 also known as TENTEN, was a rookie five-member South Korean pop girl group under Gaon Entertainment. They debuted on July 22, 2015, with their first single "Amomia". They are presumably disbanded due to inactivity since June 2016.

Originally debuting with 6 members Lee Yeeun (known as Cindy at the time) left sometime in October 2015 and Yoonah was added as a new member. In May 2016, all first-generation members left 10X10 and they came back with a new line-up, with Yoonah and two new members. The new formation was short-lived and disbanded in June 2016 without any new releases. The names of the new members remain unknown, as no announcement was made and they only participated in one concert in May.
